events.1926: City becomes capital of the Kirghiz Autonomous Socialist Soviet Republic; Pishpek renamed 'Frunze.'
events.1976: Ala Archa National Park established near city.
events.1999: The Times of Central Asia English-language newspaper begins publication.
events.2017: Turkish Airlines Flight 6491 crashes near Manas International Airport, killing 34 on the ground.
